<br>
The group was hunting outside of Paw, in SK. Our group, myself an Enchanter, a beautiful necro, and a Dwarf Pally, (stubborn but a good sword and a light heart and to whom I am truly gratful, for he put me over the top).eventully our Pally had to depart to regions unknown, so being the good, the proud and anxious casters to continue to level, I began shouting for a Tank to join our happy band of revelers.<br>
<br>
soon to appear were a druid, and a second Enchanter (who will remain nameless). Now this is going to get trickY, cause I have a beef for group tactic's, and being an Enchanter RIGHTLY SO. I as the leader began to asess the group picture, new members need to know how and when we were going to loot, and who would do what, I was about to ask my fellow Chanter, bout spliting the duties, and WHAM.. he's pulling, can u believe it?, with Tashan from a distance he cant possibly see, how many Tesh Gnollys are lurking around the spire's, the next thing I know there are 5 gnollys upon us, everyone at half life, and our newly grouped enchanter no where to be found, though his hp bub was full. the group ran, I had mezzed a couple of gnollys and began the run to Paw, but didnt make it, as a leader I bought time for my group to survive, but i didnot. Upon returning from the dead to find myself back at lvl 28 was truly dishearting, my necro and druid had survived, and grouped with a Tank, (may the Gods bless em.) and the second Enchanter no where to be found. I hope never to see him again, he will get an ear full. now on to better things.<br>
<br>
I was politly asked to group with our new tank, and greatfully accepted, he was a great leader, and listened to all our concerns, and he knew all our abilites, his Name is Rorek, he kept us informed as to the status of his buffs, and we buffed our hearts out, conserved manna when needed, we actually took out 3 gnollys, 2 were add's, I did us proud, by keeping 2 mezze'd while the group worked on 1 at a time, it was text book, it was terriffic. I also re-ding 29, /em has a happy face, and gets jiggy wit it.<br>
<br>
